contentrichtext.text: '''[[Phi]]''' (uppercase Φ, lowercase φ, or math symbol ϕ) is the 21st letter of the Greek alphabet. '''Phi''' or '''PHI''' may also refer to: {{TOCright}} ==Language== *{{IPA|ɸ}}, the symbol for [[voiceless bilabial fricative]] ==Law== * [[Protected health information]] as part of the HIPAA regulations ==Mathematics== *[[Golden ratio]], in mathematics and the arts *[[Phi coefficient]], measure of association for two binary variables introduced by Karl Pearson *[[Euler's totient function]] *A statistical measure of association reported with the [[chi-squared test]] *A function in [[static single assignment form]] == Medicine and health == * [[Protected Health Information]] * [[Paraprofessional Healthcare Institute]], a nonprofit organization based in New York City * [[Post-Polio Health International]] * Primary HIV Infection, the earliest stage of infection with [[HIV]] ==Places== * [[Philippines]] * [[Philadelphia, Pennsylvania]] * Phi, a village in [[Sesant]], Cambodia ==Science== * [[Phi meson]] * [[Phi phenomenon]] in visual perception * [[Krumbein phi scale]] for the size of a particle or sediment * [[Magnetic flux]] * [[Peptide histidine isoleucine]] * [[6-phospho-3-hexuloisomerase]], an enzyme ==Sport== * [[Philadelphia 76ers]], a National Basketball Association team * [[Philadelphia Eagles]], a National Football League team * [[Philadelphia Flyers]], a National Hockey League team * [[Philadelphia Phillies]], a Major League Baseball team ==Others== * Phi, a [[collegiate secret societies in North America#Princeton University|secret society at Princeton University]] * Phi, (Thai: {{lang|th|ผี}}), [[ghosts in Thai culture]] * [[Kamen Rider Faiz]] * [[Phi (album)|''Phi'' (album)]], a studio album by KinKi Kids * [[Packard Humanities Institute]] * [[Pepco Holdings| Pepco Holdings Inc.]] *Phi Yaan Zek, a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] [[guitarist]] who has worked with [[Ron "Bumblefoot" Thal|Bumblefoot]], [[Bryan Beller]] and [[Marco Minnemann]] among others. == See also == * [[Փ]], a letter of the Armenian alphabet {{disambiguation}} [[lt:Fi (reikšmės)]] [[simple:Phi]]
